Although '''Edwin Oswald LeGrand''' (1801–1861) was born in [[North Carolina]], he was an original [[Texas|Texan]].  LeGrand was one of the fifty-seven men who signed the [[Texas Declaration of Independence]].  He was a [[San Augustine, Texas|San Augustine]] delegate to the [[Convention of 1836]] at [[Washington-on-the-Brazos]] and fought in the [[Battle of San Jacinto]].  His sister, Mrs. William Colson Norwood, and her family also settled in San Augustine, Texas.  LeGrand is buried near San Augustine.

